feedback: Need to ask pros and cons of gas and electric vehicles.
I will NEVER consider buying an electric car! Too many horror stories. Relative bought Mustang electric. I month traded it for a real CAR
The phrasing on "name a pure electric vehicle" was a little vague to me. Almost wrote "BEV" as the designation I've heard the vehicle category called in the past.

Vehicles are too complicated 
Since we're unsafe at any SPEED why worry about all the electronic gizmos that goast brake and lead to a false sence of Safety. 
There's nothing free fair or safe.
The government shouldn't have killed off the dude that invented an engine that operated on WATER

Public transportation is expensive and uncomfortable.  EVs are poor replacements for ICEs due to range and charging limitations.  EV makers would be way ahead to focus on range management rather than acceleration.   And I own a sports car.
Try to identify limiting factors on buying decisions i.e. What is the rnge of an electric vehicle? How long does it take to charge? Does the car have a specialty use in mind when purchased.
While a BEV would support my normal driving habits very well it is too expensive to buy one just for commuting.

Crash test safety ratings are more important to me than make/model for any car.

I think electric/hybrid cars are unpopular in my region for 3 big reasons: liberal association, patchy charging infrastructure, and concerns about hurricanes (prolonged power outages, trying to evacuate, etc).
Current housing of MFH condo will NOT make a pure EV feasible. 40+ year old property that there is no realistic way to setup chargers at home location.

feedback:
I like the survey, 
clear questonare and well arranged

Some kind of question(s) to determine how much people know about how quickly the value of a vehicle goes down after purchase; gets to the decision on whether to buy used or new.  Buying slightly used gets you much more for your money.
Also the question about how we vote should have an option for "I don't vote."

Why the Latino origin questions?  Why the political questions?  

Look - Electric cars cost way more per mile to drive than a comparable gas vehicle.  Throw in the fact that mass-adoption of electric vehicles is going to wipe out most electric grids because they can’t take the drain.

They cannot be parked indoors because they can burst into flames.  They have to be handled carefully after an accident because they can burst into flames and often do.  They require thousands of tons of materials be mined out looking for Lithium.  Just because the supply chain isn’t within your purview doesn’t make it clean.  

This administration has tried to build public charging facilities to no avail after spending millions to build a handfull of facilities.

Electric cars are difficult and expensive to maintain and taking one off the beaten path where this expertise resides can lead to long-distance towing problems.

I’ll do a plug in Hybrid - but I will never do full electric.
You asked a lot of questions that have nothing to do with vehicle ownership. None were any of your business, so I marked prefer not to say.
I will never finance a vehicle again. I did once, and it was a horrid mistake.
